International tuna bodies are demanding catch limits to prevent overfishing and save tuna populations.
Japan, a major consumer, faces pressure due to its high tuna consumption.
The Tokyo-based Organisation for the Promotion of Responsible Tuna Fisheries and the World Tuna Purse Seine Organisation are calling for a moratorium on large tuna vessels.
The goal is to achieve sustainable tuna fishing practices globally.
Conservationists warn of the risk of tuna extinction and urge a radical change in fisheries management.
An international meeting aims to adopt a global action plan to monitor and protect tuna stocks.
Japan, a key player, is under scrutiny for overfishing practices.
